<br>
As far as I understand, there is a cap on how much mana you can get from items.  A while ago there was a patch that increased the total.  I &quot;think&quot; the original cap was 500 and is now 750.  Can someone confirm that or tell me the correct cap?  I don't want to waste time, plat or effort on +mana items if I am already over the cap and getting no gain from it.<br>
<br>
Thanks <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elyia>Elyia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 302<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/23/03 6:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mana Pool</span><hr size=1> A 750 cap on mana from items?  Wow I hope not considering I have around 2850 mana from items alone.  Perhaps you are thinking of +mana you can gain from buffs which was capped at 500.  I believe it has been raised.  The mana cap for items was unreachable with the current best items in the game.  The cap was raised a few patches which I guess is to prepare for the amount of mana one could get though Time items.<br>
<br>
Now there could be a cap per level in place.  Like a level 50 can only benefit from a maximum of 1000 mana from items.  But at level 65 I was not at any type of mana cap before the patch (and I had a total of 6k mana at the time) and I sure am not at it after the patch. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~kosmos00/elysig.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
